news.title: Government starts work on mapping six lakh villages, preparing 3D maps of 100 cities
news.para: The minister also drew attention to the launch of Indo ArcGIS by Esri India to address the need for ready-to-use GIS-based solution products and content in the areas of forest management, disaster management, electrical utilities, land records, water distribution and property taxation.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's buildings survey to conclude by March 1
news.para: A preliminary survey revealed last month that around 80% of buildings in the newly merged areas of Bopal-Ghuma and Kathwada and 60% in areas like Vastrapur, Thaltej, Sola, Gota and Chandlodia, which came into AMC limits in 2006, do not have BU permission.

news.title: Got houses but not homes: Displaced Chintels Paradiso families
news.para: The department of town and country planning (DTCP), on the directions of chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar, is overseeing the rehabilitation process of these families.

news.title: Housing ministry gives nod for construction of 60,000 houses under PMAY
news.para: Proposals were approved for construction of more than 60,000 houses in Andhra Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Himachal Pradesh, Karnataka and Rajasthan, the statement stated.

news.title: Over 1.12 lakh land conversion requests pending in Kerala
news.para: The steep increase in the applications for land conversion pending in various revenue offices has been noticed ever since the government decided not to charge any fee for the conversion of the land up to 25 cents.

news.title: ACC commissions 1.6-MTPA grinding unit at Tikaria in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: ACC MD and CEO Sridhar Balakrishnan said, "ACC's strong belief and resilience in these difficult times enabled the team to commission the additional capacity at Tikaria GU."

news.title: MahaRERA division office sought in Aurangabad
news.para: Currently, the real estate sector regulator is headquartered in Mumbai forcing stakeholders from Aurangabad to travel all the way to the state capital to resolve their dispute.

news.title: Noida: Income tax department raids SD Properties premises
news.para: “On Tuesday morning, an I-T team searched Singh’s office SD Properties in Sector 10. During the search, the team unearthed various tax evasion measures he had adopted, an officer said.

news.title: DTCP writes to IIT-Delhi for Chintels Paradiso audit
news.para: In a letter, district town planner (enforcement) RS Batth has sought the advice of IIT experts on whether the towers are safe to live in or not and whether any defects, if found, are repairable. Batth has also sought recommendation on the methodology to be adopted for repairs.

news.title: Telangana: House owners lose lakhs in QR code frauds, 'reverse' payment
news.para: Top police officers said several employees of multi-national companies are failing to see through the dirty tricks of fraudsters, who are siphoning off lakhs of rupees by either asking house owners to scan QR codes or receive rental advance through what is described as ‘reverse payment' method that doesn't exist.

news.title: Yes Bank scam: CBI searches underway at six locations
news.para: Radius Group was one of the biggest borrowers on the erstwhile DHFL with an outstanding loan with interest of around Rs 3,000 crores for a residential project in suburban Mumbai. The project is a joint venture between Radius and Sumer Group.

news.title: Delhi HC to pass order on Ansal brothers' pleas on Feb 16
news.para: The bench of Justice Subramonium Prasad will pass the judgment on Wednesday. The court had kept the order reserved on January 27, 2022 after the conclusion of the submissions of all sides.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso's builder charged with culpable homicide
news.para: ​A senior officer confirmed on Tuesday that the charge has been added to the first FIR registered in connection with the February 10 incident at Bajghera police station.

news.title: Chinese developer Grandjoy gets $1.6 billion facility to fund M&A
news.para: Grandjoy said on its official account on WeChat late on Monday the facility would support its acquisitions and come in the form of loans, funds, securitisation and other financing products.

news.title: NBCC's net profit down 10% to Rs 87 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income also fell to Rs 2,056.31 crore in the third quarter of the fiscal from Rs 2,149.17 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.
